President Obama held a briefing with key members of his response team to discuss preparations for the 2013 hurricane season. The President received an update on the hurricane season outlook and heard from various officials about efforts to prepare for the season and lessons learned from previous hurricanes, including Hurricane Sandy. The meeting also focused on the impacts on the electric and petroleum sectors following Hurricane Sandy and the coordination between federal, state, local, and private sector partners to address fuel shortages. The President emphasized the importance of preparedness and coordination among all stakeholders and directed his team to apply lessons learned from Hurricane Sandy to improve response efforts. The meeting included representatives from various departments and agencies, including the Department of Homeland Security, FEMA, Department of Energy, Department of Transportation, EPA, and the National Hurricane Center.